fact WorkItem(
  id: "WI-075",
  description: "LogicalQuery disjunction via push_choice primitive (design refined 2026-04-23). Replace the kb/execute.rs:381 NotYetImplemented with: (1) generalize Candidate enum in kb/resolve.rs to add Continuation(Vec<TermId>) variant alongside Rule/Occurrence — the existing FrameState::ChoicePoint machinery iterates Candidates so this is local and reuses all alts/dedup/solution-accounting code; (2) add new top-level namespace anthill.kernel as the home for resolver primitives (qualified namespace replaces sigil prefix — consistent with anthill.reflect.*); (3) declare 'operation push_choice(?goal: Term) -> Bool' in stdlib/anthill/kernel/kernel.anthill; (4) add BuiltinTag::PushChoice in kb/mod.rs:27, register as 'anthill.kernel.push_choice' in register_standard_builtins (mod.rs:1656); (5) handle PushChoice in step_init (not execute_builtin — same special-case pattern as Not/HoApply): walk the argument to get alt_goal, transform current Frame from Init to ChoicePoint with two Continuation candidates: cont_a = goals[1..] (drop push_choice from queue), cont_b = [alt_goal, ...goals[2..]] — existing iteration handles 'try cont_a; on backtrack try cont_b'; (6) add stdlib rule 'or(?a, ?b) :- push_choice(?b), ?a' (variables-in-goal-position already work since step_init walks goals through substitution); (7) wire kb/execute.rs disjunction(L, R) lowering to emit or(L_goal, R_goal), wrapping multi-goal branches in conjunction-rule (same pattern as negation, kb/execute.rs:356). Tests: basic disjunction yields both branches; disjunction inside conjunction (no DNF push-down needed — falls out of frame structure); nested disjunctions; shared variables across branches; long-stream variant once WI-077 lands. Foundational scope: push_choice is the substrate for the future Branch effect in functional operation bodies (proposal 026/M5) — a Branch(a, b) effect with 'collect all paths' handler raises an equivalent push_choice at the resolver layer, so the same primitive serves both rule-body disjunction and expression-level nondeterminism. Cut, soft-cut, if-then-else, once, findall are similarly downstream. Background: kb/execute.rs:381 currently returns LowerError::NotYetImplemented('disjunction (resolver has no native OR; needs rule-lifting)'). See docs/status/wi-047.md.",
  acceptance: [ToolPasses("cargo-test")],
  depends_on: ["WI-047"],
  status: Open)

